                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Hangman</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/28/2003&nbsp;: 02:31:04 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> What is wrong with you people?  I was soloing here at 51 and you can too.<br /><br />Here is what you do.  First make pet and turn off taunt. Then get full mana and around 80 health if under 53.  Pull with darkness.  If it fails run far ahead with jboots or sow.  I used jboots and recast it.  I always would run out of range of spell then cast again.  IF snare fails 2 or 3 times sic pet.  You have enough agro and a bash will help you land snare.<br /><br />Once snare is landed this is what I would cast.  First, i would use ignite blood as it was never resisted, then splurt, then plague, aystole and then ebolt.  As soon as aystole landed, sic pet if snare landed early.<br /><br />Run far ahead and sit to med with lich.  As soon as ebolt runs out resnare.  You have 3 tries to get it off if all spells where not resisted between snare and ebolt.  After you re snare reebolt.  Run far ahead and med again.  This time when ebolt wears off BoD it and run ahead.  When Ignitre blood wears off resnare.  At this time it is near dead and will start stand still.  Sit and med and let pet beat it up.<br /><br />You can do this method with 162 int, that is what i had and 1k hps self buffed.  I could solo the white con ravens at 51 and then again at 52.  At 53 use the new rogue pet.  Also instead of ravens kill trees.  They are white and are less resistant to spells than the bugs.<br /><br />Also, look up Chrisitine's guide for fear kiting in PoN.  Get a full split group and solo here.  A bard, who is a rl friend in a full split group soloing in PoN at 51 was getting 2 blue per kill per raven.  She went through 51-63 and is halfway through 64 in a split group in PoN. Granted she can swarm kite, but the wolves camp mobs are lower level.  I have almost kept up with her soloing at the fear kite spot and get much faster xp when I solo gargs, which can be done at 56.<br /><br />Don't give up cause you failed one time.  I died many times over, but I also got more XP in 2 kills than in 3 deaths.</span></font></td>
