                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Devyls Advokate</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/26/2003&nbsp;: 7:38:13 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Jus' a tip on soloing PoN:<br /><br />I have been soloing off and on here from 53 until my current lvl of 59, in fact, I just finged last night here on a tree, but I digress.  The best spot I have found to solo kite in PoN is just to the right from zone in.  Basically, upon zoning in, turn right and follow the hill/wall down a little bit.  You will see a large tree that looks like a treant but is just a tree.  You will see what I mean when you see it, its one hella fugly tree.  <br /><br />Anyways, nothing paths here so go ahead and haste pet (turning taunt off, of course) and park him at the base of his tree.  you now have 2 options.  Option one, follow up the zone wall a bit further and you will see teh first static spawn, normally a spider or a burd, but it also pops as a tree sometimes.  Farther up the vally from him are 2 more static trees.  The cool thing about these mobs is there placement as statics, rather than wanderers, enables you to FD off a resist on snare without running like a dr00d who just got his feet shaved with a dull razor.  Option 2 is to head out into the yard trash milling around the middle of the zone, I normally don't do this until I have keeled all teh statics.<br /><br />Another thing that may prove useful, don't send the pet until you have the mob down to 80% health, this will ensure you have agro and save you bonechips (expensive as they are).  Also, make sure you are stacking dots appropriately, its a waste of mana to drop a dot if it is only gonna last 3 ticks.  At 55, I normally kept a rotation of Splurt, BoD, Ignite Blood, and Snare (Use dooming, even with a ceramic skull Cascading takes too long).  If I was feeling cheeky, I would throw plague in as well, just to mix things up.  Once you hit 56, change out CoC for EBolt and add Demi and you will be a machine.<br /><br />Sorry I ended up writing a book on this, I hope it proves useful.<br /><br />Stay (un)safe,<br /><br />Dev<br /><br /><br /><br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
